            "body": "v4.31.0 migration fix patterns (Cech + GR push-pull/pullback proofs)\n\nEffective repairs for the **v4.31.0 defeq-transparency-wall** breaks in these projects:\n\n- **Port from the AJC copy first.** `MainProjects/Algebraic-Jacobian-Challenge/.../<same file>` is often already sorry-free (e.g. `PresheafCech.lean`, `CechSectionIdentificationBase.lean`). `diff` the subproject vs AJC; if they differ only in the sorry regions, copy the AJC file wholesale.\n- **`set_option backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false in`** before a lemma fixes most \"type mismatch under instances transparency\" / stuck defeq. **Placement matters**: it must go BEFORE the docstring `/-- \u2026 -/`, never between docstring and `lemma` (that is a parse error: \"unexpected token 'set_option'; expected 'lemma'\"). Stacks with `set_option maxHeartbeats N in`.\n- **`erw [Category.comp_id]` / `erw [Category.id_comp]`** closes residual `A \u226b \ud835\udfd9 = A` / `\ud835\udfd9 \u226b A = A` when the `\ud835\udfd9`'s object is only defeq (e.g. `(\ud835\udfed).obj M` vs `M`, or a `\u22d9`-form) so `simp`/`exact Category.comp_id _` fail. `erw` matches through the wall then auto-`rfl`.\n- **`rw [reassoc_of% h1, reassoc_of% h2]` ordering**: cancel the INNER hom\u226binv pair first so the outer pair becomes adjacent.\n- **`subst h; simp <;> rfl`** for eqToHom-transport lemmas whose two sides reduce to defeq-but-not-syntactic `map = map`.\n- **LSP is dead** on these full-`import Mathlib` files (server crashes / broken pipe). Iterate with `lake build <module>` and read the printed unsolved-goal state from the error output. `GlueDescent` \u2248 2.6 min/build; `CechHigherDirectImage` \u2248 8.5 min/build.",
